}}</ref>

1933年8月由上海申报馆初版中国最早的现代地图集——[[丁文江|丁文江]]、[[翁文灏|翁文灏]]、[[曾世英|曾世英]]编纂的《中华民国新地图》及其缩印本《中国分省新图》，在其西藏图幅的中、尼交界处，喜马拉雅山脉中段那座标高8840公尺的山峰被注名为英文之汉字译写形式——“挨佛拉斯峰”。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ctr.sisu.edu.cn/info/1653/1192.htm|title=“珠穆朗玛峰”的得名及其他|website=四川外国语大学地名研究中心}}</ref>

1951年，[[暨南大学|暨南大学]]地理学教授[[王鞠侯|王鞠侯]]在《开明少年》发表《大小高低》一文，建议命名为“珠-{}-穆朗玛峰”。引起《人民日报》编辑[[胡仲持|胡仲持]]的注意”。经[[中国科学院|中国科学院]]副院长[[竺可桢|竺可桢]]建议、北京大学教授[[林超_(1909年)|林超]]查阅故宫档案及外文资料考证核实，[[中央人民政府内务部|中央人民政府内务部]]、[[出版总署|出版总署]]于1952年5月8日发布通报，将“额菲尔士峰”定名为“珠穆朗玛峰”，同时将“外喜马拉雅山”定名为“[[冈底斯山|冈底斯山]]”。1952年5月27日，《人民日报》刊发《中央人民政府内务部、出版总署通报“额菲尔士峰”应名为“珠穆朗玛峰”，“外喜马拉雅山”应名为“冈底斯山”》。<ref>{{Cite web|title=56年前的今天　珠穆朗玛峰得以“正名”--奥运|url=http://2008.people.com.cn/GB/116565/7215798.html|accessdate=2019-11-30|work=人民网|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200209010125/http://2008.people.com.cn/GB/116565/7215798.html|archive-date=2020-02-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>2002年，[[人民日报|人民日报]]刊文，认为英文名“Mount Everest”应改为藏语名“Mount Qomolangma”（「珠穆朗瑪峰」）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.people.cn/200211/19/eng20021119_107017.shtml|title=No Longer Everest but Mount Qomolangma|website=人民日报|access-date=2020-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200519091753/http://en.people.cn/200211/19/eng20021119_107017.shtml|archive-date=2020-05-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>

「珠穆朗玛」的音意，一说意为“神女第三”，珠穆（{{藏|ཇོ་མོ}}）意为女神，朗玛意为第三，因珠峰附近还有四座山峰，珠峰位于第三。一说“大地的女神”，“玛”是陰[[性_(語法)|性]][[詞類|詞類]][[名詞化|名詞化]]，“朗玛”（lang ma，{{藏|གླང་མ}}）的意義有不同說法：一為[[藏傳佛教|藏傳佛教]]传说[[長壽五天女|長壽五天女]]中居於此峰的[[荼吉尼|天女]]「米玉洛桑瑪」（Miyo lang sangma，貞慧天女）的略稱，一為「母牛」，一為「母[[象|象]]」。<ref name="RGS2003">{{cite book|author=Royal Geographical Society|location=Great Britain|title=''Everest: Summit of Achievement''|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8ph67BBsPkwC&pg=PA58|year=2003|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-0-7432-4386-5|pages=58–60}}{{en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=''Mount Everest - mountain, Asia''|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Mount-Everest|author=(Cuthbert) Wilfrid (Francis) Noyce, (Henry Cecil) John Hunt, Barry C. Bishop, Norgay Tenzing, Stephen Venables|work=[[大英百科全書|大英百科全書]]|dead-url=no|access-date=2017-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818094956/https://www.britannica.com/place/Mount-Everest|archive-date=2017-08-18}}{{en}}</ref><ref name="Lewis2015">{{cite book|author=Jon E. Lewis|title=''The Mammoth Book Of Everest: From the first attempts to today, 40 first-hand accounts''| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jvF0DQAAQBAJ&pg=PT14|date=2015-06-04| publisher=Little, Brown Book Group| isbn=978-1-4721-2019-9| pages=14–16}}{{en}}</ref><ref name="natgeo1">{{cite magazine|last=Coburn|first=Broughton|title=''Mount Everest Fight Raises Questions About Sherpas''|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2013/13/130501-mount-everest-fight-sherpas-sahibs-world-mountain-climbing/|magazine=《[[國家地理_(雜誌)|國家地理]]》|date=2013-05-01|accessdate=2017-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706084800/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2013/13/130501-mount-everest-fight-sherpas-sahibs-world-mountain-climbing/|archive-date=2017-07-06|dead-url=no}}{{en}}</ref><ref name="CarreraMallarach2008">{{cite book|author1=Josep Maria Mallarach |title=''Protected Landscapes and Cultural and Spiritual Values'' |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NXWxbvFEi8sC&pg=PA78| year=2008|publisher=Kasparek Verlag|isbn=978-3-925064-60-9|pages=73,78}}{{en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=彼得．祖克曼、阿曼達．帕多安(Peter Zuckerman、Amanda Padoan)|title=K2峰: 天堂之門與雪巴人的故事|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E3_2CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA36|date=2016-03-31|publisher=紅樹林| isbn=978-986-7885-80-7| page=36}}</ref>。

西方世界对珠峰的称呼，1733年，法國地理學家{{link-en|丹威爾|Jean-Baptiste Bourguignon d'Anville}}參考《康熙皇輿全覽圖》，采用藏语名称为Tschoumou-Lanckma（珠穆朗瑪）。<ref name="李孝聰"/>{{rp|78}}<ref>{{cite journal | title=''The China Maps of Jean-Baptiste Bourguignon d&apos;Anville: Origins and Supporting Networks'' | author=Mario Cams | journal=The International Journal for the History of Cartography | volume=66 | date=2014 | issue=1 | pages=51-69 | url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/03085694.2014.845949 | access-date=2017-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203190245/https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/03085694.2014.845949 | archive-date=2019-02-03 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref><ref name="Gillman2000"/>1865年前，西方称为第十五峰（Peak XV）。1865年后，命名為'''額菲爾士峰'''或'''埃佛勒斯峰'''（Mount Everest）。1856年，英属{{link-en|印度測量局局長|Surveyor General of India}}{{link-en|安德魯·史考特·華歐|Andrew Scott Waugh}}宣称命名为「埃佛勒斯」以紀念他的老師、前任局長[[喬治·埃佛勒斯|喬治·埃佛勒斯]]。埃佛勒斯本人表示反對并告知英国皇家地理學會[[印地語|印地語]]不能拼寫“埃佛勒斯”，印度本地人也不會念，{{link-en|布萊恩·霍顿·霍奇森|Brian Houghton Hodgson}}指出此峰尼泊爾當地名稱為Deodhunga（聖山）。儘管如此，1865年，英国皇家地理學會仍采用「埃佛勒斯峰」名称。<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://old.harappa.com/engr/darjeeling.html | title=''TEA IN INDIA. - DEODHUNGA, THE HIGHEST MOUNTAIN IN THE WORLD'' | newspaper=《[[倫敦新聞畫報|倫敦新聞畫報]]》| date=1857-08-15 | pages=168-170| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071226022726/http://www.harappa.com/engr/darjeeling.html | archivedate=1997-02-05}}{{en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal| title=''Papers relating to the Himalaya and Mount Everest''| journal=Proceedings of the London Royal Geographical Society of London| volume=IX| pages=345–351| date=April–May 1857| url=http://pahar.in/wpfb-file/1857-papers-relating-to-the-himalaya-and-mount-everest-from-prgsv1-s-pdf/| quote=…I was taught by my respected chief and predecessor, Colonel Sir Geo. Everest to assign to every geographical object its true local or native appellation. … But here is a mountain, most probably the highest in the world, without any local name that we can discover, whose native appellation, if it has any, will not very likely be ascertained before we are allowed to penetrate into Nepal.… In the meantime the privilege as well as the duty devolves on me to assign…a name whereby it may be known among citizens and geographers and become a household word among civilized nations.| author=| access-date=2017-07-10| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203190245/http://pahar.in/wpfb-file/1857-papers-relating-to-the-himalaya-and-mount-everest-from-prgsv1-s-pdf/| archive-date=2019-02-03| dead-url=no}}{{en}}（翻译：我尊敬的领导和前任乔治·埃佛勒斯局长曾经教我给每个地理物体它真正的当地或本地称呼……但是这座山，很可能世界最高，没有任何我们能发现的当地称呼，它的本地称呼，如果有，也不可能在我们进尼泊尔之前而确定。其间，荣幸的分配任务交代了给我……一个市民和地理学家都知道的、文明社会里家喻户晓的名字。）</ref><ref name="Gillman2000"/><ref name="Lewis2015" />。

[[尼泊尔语|尼泊尔语]]中称呼珠峰，过去只有當地名稱而沒有官方名稱，使得尼泊爾在與{{link-en|中尼邊界談判|China–Nepal border|中國邊界談判}}中處於不利地位。尼泊爾政府於1956年採用'''萨迦玛塔峰'''（{{lang|ne|सगरमाथा}}：{{transl|ne|Sagarmāthā}}）為官方名稱，此名來自當地使用的[[吠陀梵語|吠陀梵語]]<ref name="Telegraph Weekly" />，{{transl|ne|sagar}}意為「天空」，{{transl|ne|māthā}}意為「頭」，「薩迦瑪塔」的意思是「天空的額頭」<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.sagarmathanationalpark.gov.np/index.php/2014-06-03-06-27-06/establishment | title=''Establishment'' | publisher=[[薩加瑪塔國家公園|薩加瑪塔國家公園]] | access-date=2017-07-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622023800/http://www.sagarmathanationalpark.gov.np/index.php/2014-06-03-06-27-06/establishment | archive-date=2017-06-22 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref>。尼泊爾著名歷史學家Baburam Acharya於1938年發表文章，指出當地一直稱呼此峰為{{transl|ne|Sagarmāthā}}。<ref name="Telegraph Weekly">{{Cite news | url=http://www.telegraphnepal.com/national/2015-03-25/nepal-and-china-make-claims-over-mount-everest-or-sagarmatha-.html | title=''Nepal and China make claims over Mount Everest or Sagarmatha?'' | author=Buddhi Narayan Shrestha, Senior Border Expert, Nepal | newspaper=The Telegraph Weekly | location=尼泊爾 | access-date=2017-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150720040349/http://www.telegraphnepal.com/national/2015-03-25/nepal-and-china-make-claims-over-mount-everest-or-sagarmatha-.html | archive-date=2015-07-20 | dead-url=no }} 參見{{cite book | title=''Border Management of Nepal'' | url=https://indiamadhesi.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/border-management-of-nepal.pdf | format=PDF | year=2003 | author=Buddhi Narayan Shrestha | isbn=978-9993357421 | publisher=Bhumichitra | access-date=2017-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203190245/https://indiamadhesi.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/border-management-of-nepal.pdf | archive-date=2019-02-03 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref><ref name="Unsworth1989">{{cite book|author=Walt Unsworth|title=''Everest: The Mountaineering History''| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hvgOAQAAMAAJ| year=1989| publisher=Grafton| isbn=978-0-586-20626-3| page=550}}{{en}}</ref><ref name="西藏旅游网" />

