珠穆朗玛峰高大巍峨的形象一直在当地甚至全世界的范围内产生着影响。當地的[[雪巴人|雪巴人]]相信，珠穆朗瑪峰南面是[[蓮花生|蓮花生]]大士指定的{{link-en|隱密聖地|beyul}}之一，蓮花生大士降伏了喜馬拉雅山區的[[苯教|苯教]][[長壽五天女|長壽五天女]]皈依佛教，守護此地。<ref>{{Cite magazine | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2013/13/130501-mount-everest-fight-sherpas-sahibs-world-mountain-climbing/ | title=''Mount Everest Fight Raises Questions About Sherpas'' | date=2013-05-01 | magazine=《[[国家地理_(杂志)|國家地理]]》 | access-date=2017-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706084800/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2013/13/130501-mount-everest-fight-sherpas-sahibs-world-mountain-climbing/ | archive-date=2017-07-06 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref><ref name="PowersTempleman2012">{{cite book|author1=John Powers|author2=David Templeman|title=''Historical Dictionary of Tibet''| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wksCKIivSNUC&pg=PA620| year=2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-6805-2| pages=620–621}}</ref><ref name="CarreraMallarach2008_2">{{cite book|author=Josep Maria Mallarach | title=''Protected Landscapes and Cultural and Spiritual Values''| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NXWxbvFEi8sC&pg=PA68| year=2008| publisher=Kasparek Verlag|isbn=978-3-925064-60-9|pages=68, 70-71}}</ref>珠峰北面的[[絨布寺|絨布寺]]是世界上海拔最高的寺廟<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tibet.cn/newzt/rsxzzt/xzsm/t20050705_40482.htm |title=絨布寺——世界上海拔最高的寺廟 |access-date=2017-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222061454/http://www.tibet.cn/newzt/rsxzzt/xzsm/t20050705_40482.htm |archive-date=2014-02-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，景觀壯闊，它曾是當地最大的寺廟<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/everest/history/rongbukmon.html | title=''Rongbuk Monastery'' | access-date=2017-07-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170727074123/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/everest/history/rongbukmon.html | archive-date=2017-07-27 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref>，也是雪巴人重要的朝聖地點。<ref name="NorkeyUllman1956">{{cite book|author1=Norkey Tenzing Norkey|author2=James Ramsey Ullman|title=Man of Everest: The Autobiography of Tenzing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iJR6nQEACAAJ|year=1956|publisher=Reprint Society|access-date=2017-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170208141603/https://books.google.com/books?id=iJR6nQEACAAJ|archive-date=2017-02-08|dead-url=no}}{{en}}</ref>

中华人民共和国的第四版[[人民币|人民币]]十元[[鈔票|鈔票]]的背面便是珠穆朗玛峰。<ref name="庄??2007">{{cite book| author=莊銘國| title=典藏鈔票異數| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6BbCTwWVlXoC&pg=PA24| year=2007|publisher=五南圖書|isbn=978-957-11-4346-0|page=24}}</ref>[[新西蘭元|新西蘭元]]五元鈔票的正面是珠穆朗瑪峰首次登頂者[[艾德蒙·希拉里|艾德蒙·希拉蕊]]的肖像，以鼓勵國人冒險犯難之精神。<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.rbnz.govt.nz/notes-and-coins/notes/banknotes-in-circulation/banknote-features-for-each-denomination/5-dollars | title=''Details of the security features, size and images used on the $5 banknote.'' | publisher=Reserve Bank of New Zealand | access-date=2017-07-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730132719/http://www.rbnz.govt.nz/notes-and-coins/notes/banknotes-in-circulation/banknote-features-for-each-denomination/5-dollars | archive-date=2017-07-30 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rbnz.govt.nz/notes-and-coins/notes/banknotes-in-circulation | title=''Banknotes in circulation'' | publisher=Reserve Bank of New Zealand | access-date=2017-07-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715113920/http://www.rbnz.govt.nz/notes-and-coins/notes/banknotes-in-circulation | archive-date=2017-07-15 | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref>全世界造價最貴的[[雲霄飛車|雲霄飛車]]以珠峰為主題，位於美國[[佛羅里達州|佛羅里達州]][[迪士尼動物王國|迪士尼動物王國]]，稱為「埃佛勒斯峰歷險—禁山之傳奇」（Expedition Everest-Legend of the Forbidden Mountain），雲霄飛車中途會遇上[[雪人_(傳說生物)|雪人]]襲擊。<ref name="Records2010">{{cite book|title=''Guinness World Records 2011''|year=2010|
url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bLlrRQAACAAJ| publisher=[[吉尼斯世界纪录大全|Guinness World Records]]| isbn=978-1-904994-58-9 |page=366}}{{en}}</ref>[[2008年夏季奧林匹克運動會火炬接力|2008年夏季奧林匹克運動會火炬接力]]登上珠穆朗瑪峰。[[金庸|金庸]]的武俠小說《[[神鵰俠侶|神鵰俠侶]]》中，[[金輪國師|金輪法王]]對[[郭襄|郭襄]]自稱是「珠穆朗瑪」，暗示自己武功高絕、無人可及。<ref>《神鵰俠侶37・三世恩怨》：郭襄俏臉上一陣紅暈，笑問：“大和尚，你叫甚么法名啊？”法王道：“我叫珠穆朗瑪。”珠穆朗瑪是西藏境內一座高山之名，此峰極高，天下第一，法王隨口說了出來，隱有武功高絕、無人可及之意。</ref>

